60|$|But he knew Mother's way of {{sticking}} to an idea, {{and he began}} to persuade himself that Saserkopee was a haven of refuge. Whenever they seemed to be having a peaceful discussion of Lulu Hartwig's canary-yellow sweater, they were <b>hearing</b> <b>her</b> <b>voice,</b> wondering if they could tolerate its twangy comments the rest of their lives.|$|R
