5000|$|More recently, John Dickson has {{questioned}} {{the meaning of}} the word didaskō ("teach"). Dickson argues that it refers to [...] "preserving and laying down the traditions handed on by the apostles". Dickson goes on to argue that since that does not happen in most sermons today, women are not prohibited from giving sermons. Dickson's argument has been criticized in Women, Sermons and the Bible: Essays interacting with John Dickson's <b>Hearing</b> <b>Her</b> <b>Voice,</b> published by Matthias Media.|$|R
